  "response_text": "Here is a comprehensive, healthy meal prep plan designed for **variety, balance, and efficiency**. It focuses on whole foods, lean proteins, healthy fats, and complex carbohydrates.\n\nThis plan is for **5 days** (Monday-Friday) and assumes you will cook on **Sunday** for about 2-3 hours.\n\n### The Core Principles of This Plan:\n\n- **Balanced Macros:** Each meal includes protein (for satiety), fiber (for digestion), and healthy fats (for hormone function).\n- **Batch Cooking:** We cook large components (grains, proteins, veggies) and assemble them differently to avoid boredom.\n- **Portion Control:** Use divided meal prep containers (3-compartment is ideal).\n- **Flexibility:** Swap veggies or proteins based on what's on sale or in season.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: The Sunday \"Big Cook\" (2-3 hours)\n\nCook these base components. Store them in separate airtight containers in the fridge.\n\n**Proteins (Choose 2-3):**\n1.  **Grilled Chicken Breast (x4):** Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika. Grill or bake at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 mins.\n2.  **Lean Ground Turkey (1 lb):** Brown with onion, garlic, cumin, and chili powder.\n3.  **Hard-Boiled Eggs (x6):** Perfect for snacks or quick breakfasts.\n4.  **Canned Chickpeas (rinsed & drained):** No cooking needed; great for salads.\n\n**Grains & Starches:**\n1.  **Quinoa (2 cups dry):** Cooks in 15 mins. Fluff with a fork.\n2.  **Sweet Potatoes (x3 large):** Roast at 400°F (200°C) for 30-40 mins until tender. Cut into cubes.\n\n**Vegetables (Roast or Steam):**\n1.  **Broccoli & Bell Peppers:** Toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on a sheet pan for 20 mins at 400°F.\n2.  **Cherry Tomatoes & Zucchini:** Roast separately or together.\n3.  **Pre-washed Salad Greens (e.g., spinach, arugula):** Keep fresh in the bag.\n\n**Sauces & Dressings (Make 2):**\n1.  **Lemon-Tahini Dressing:** 3 tbsp tahini + juice of 1 lemon + 2 tbsp water + 1 clove garlic (minced) + salt. Whisk.\n2.  **Simple Vinaigrette:** 3 tbsp olive oil + 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar + 1 tsp Dijon mustard + salt & pepper.\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: The 5-Day Meal Prep Plan\n\n*(P = Protein / G = Grain / V = Veggie / F = Fat)*\n\n| Day | Breakfast (Grab & Go) | Lunch (Container 1) | Dinner (Container 2) | Snack (Optional) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Monday** | **Overnight Oats:** 1/2 cup oats + 1 cup almond milk + 1 tbsp chia seeds + berries. | **Chicken Quinoa Bowl:** Grilled chicken + quinoa + roasted broccoli + 2 tbsp lemon-tahini dressing. | **Turkey & Sweet Potato:** Ground turkey + roasted sweet potato cubes + sautéed spinach (1 min in pan). | 1 hard-boiled egg + 1 apple. |\n| **Tuesday** | **Greek Yogurt Parfait:** 1 cup plain Greek yogurt + 1/2 cup berries + 1 tbsp almonds. | **Leftover Turkey Bowl:** Turkey + quinoa + roasted bell peppers + a handful of fresh spinach. | **Chickpea Salad:** Chickpeas + chopped cucumber + cherry tomatoes + feta cheese + vinaigrette. | 1/2 avocado with salt & pepper. |\n| **Wednesday**| **Overnight Oats** (from Monday) | **Chicken Salad Wrap:** Shredded chicken + 2 tbsp Greek yogurt + diced apple + celery. Wrap in a large lettuce leaf or whole wheat tortilla. | **Sheet Pan Remix:** Roasted sweet potato + roasted broccoli + leftover chicken + drizzle of tahini. | Handful of almonds. |\n| **Thursday** | **Scrambled Eggs (quick):** 2 eggs + spinach + 1 slice whole grain toast. | **Leftover Chickpea Salad** (from Tuesday) | **Turkey & Quinoa Stuffed Pepper:** (Use leftover turkey & quinoa; stuff into a raw bell pepper half—easy no-cook). | 1 hard-boiled egg + 1 pear. |\n| **Friday** | **Greek Yogurt Parfait** (from Tuesday) | **\"Kitchen Sink\" Bowl:** Leftover quinoa + any remaining veggies + chickpeas + hard-boiled egg + vinaigrette. | **Quick Salmon (if you have time):** Pan-sear a salmon fillet (5 mins) + leftover sweet potato + steamed green beans. | 1/2 cup cottage cheese + berries. |\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Shopping List (for the week)\n\n**Produce:**\n- 4 chicken breasts (or 1.5 lbs)\n- 1 lb lean ground turkey\n- 2 large sweet potatoes\n- 1 head of broccoli\n- 2 bell peppers (any color)\n- 1 pint cherry tomatoes\n- 1 zucchini\n- 1 lemon\n- 1 bag fresh spinach\n- 1 bag pre-washed salad greens (or arugula)\n- 1 cucumber\n- 1 apple\n- 1 pear\n- 1 bag frozen berries (or fresh)\n- 1 avocado\n\n**Pantry & Canned Goods:**\n- 1 can chickpeas (15 oz)\n- 1 cup dry quinoa\n- 1 cup rolled oats\n- 1 tbsp chia seeds\n- Almonds (raw, unsalted)\n- Olive oil, balsamic vinegar\n- Spices: Salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika, cumin, chili powder\n\n**Dairy & Alternatives:**\n- 1 carton almond milk (or milk of choice)\n- 1 large tub plain Greek yogurt (2% or full fat)\n- 1 block feta cheese (optional)\n- 1 dozen eggs\n- 1 tub cottage cheese (optional)\n\n**Fridge Staples:**\n- Tahini (sesame paste)\n- Dijon mustard\n\n### Pro-Tips for Success:\n\n1.  **Don't overcomplicate spices.** Salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika work for almost everything.\n2.  **Use the freezer.** If you get tired of a meal by Thursday, freeze the last portion for next week.\n3.  **Wet vs. Dry.** Store dressing *separately* from greens and grains to prevent sogginess. Add dressing only when you're about to eat.\n4.  **Microwave & Add Fresh.** When reheating, microwave the protein",
